<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-19T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-19T22:00:00-05:00" n="268" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d268">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/32649:
                        Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-19T23:00:00-04:00">January 19,
                                1944—11 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>91. Your 83 of January 10, midnight. Should Hewitt still be in Stockholm, you
                        are instructed to inform him that Kersten’s proposition should not even be
                        considered. For Hewitt’s information the only terms which this Government is
                        prepared to give are those of unconditional surrender. The substance of this
                        “peace feeler” will be communicated to the British and Soviet Embassies
                            here.<note n="54" xml:id="d268fn54">This was done by <hi rend="italic">aide-mêmoire</hi> dated January 24, 1944, not printed; see footnote
                            40, <ref target="#pg_491">p. 491</ref>.</note>
                    </p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>